{"_id":"0927803d41163d72","name":"Sign from the Browne Family","type":"clue","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-symbol-shield.webp","system":{"description":"A weathered sign next to a tool shed in the abandoned apple orchard that reads 'Gift courtesy of the Browne family.' This sign is evidence of Arthur, Clarence, and Frank Browne's previous community leadership and their efforts to provide employment and support for Whitehaven's residents before Bardolf Greed's arrival. The orchard once employed many inhabitants of Whitehaven and represents the brothers' former dedication to the town's welfare - a stark contrast to their current violent rebellion as the Pig Heads gang.","location":"The apple orchard outside Whitehaven","importance":"minor","found":false,"scenario":"the-city-of-pigs"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"176a40c504eeae0a","name":"The Brand of Greed","type":"object","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-sealed-red-brown.webp","system":{"description":"A special pass granted by Bardolf Greed only to those who demonstrate exceptional cunning and ability, earning his trust and respect. The Brand of Greed provides free access to any place in Whitehaven - including the factories, mine, and slaughterhouse - without any person in charge being able to object to the bearer's entrance. This document represents Bardolf's personal endorsement and carries significant weight among the city's workers and guards. Possessing this Brand allows one to exploit its importance when dealing with city dwellers.","quantity":1,"weight":0.1,"value":100,"equipped":false,"properties":["Official document","All-access pass","Bardolf's endorsement","Authority symbol"]},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"3fb41c3c618e2073","name":"Rusty Key to the Slaughterhouse","type":"object","img":"icons/sundries/misc/key-simple-metal-brown.webp","system":{"description":"A rusty old key found in Clarence's shack in the apple orchard. The key is labeled 'slaughterhouse' and grants access to Frank Browne's workplace where he secretly mixes the flesh of The God Under the Mine with common meat to infect unsuspecting miners. This key is crucial evidence linking Clarence to the Pig Heads gang and their operations at the slaughterhouse.","quantity":1,"weight":0.5,"value":10,"equipped":false,"properties":["Unlocks slaughterhouse","Evidence of conspiracy","Rusty and old"]},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"5e08845f11bad032","name":"Map of the Mine with Marked Well","type":"clue","img":"icons/sundries/documents/blueprint-damaged.webp","system":{"description":"A sketched map of Whitehaven's mine found in Clarence's shack in the orchard. The map has a specific point marked with the word 'well' - indicating the location of a narrow shaft that leads down to Arthur Browne's hidden cave. This is the secret entrance to The God Under the Mine's chamber, where Arthur has been living since the mine collapse that supposedly killed him. The map shows abandoned areas of the mine and the exact location of the vertical tunnel Frank dug to communicate with his trapped brother.","location":"Clarence's shack in the apple orchard","importance":"crucial","found":false,"scenario":"the-city-of-pigs"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"5e79ca1208f73823","name":"William's Black Leather Book","type":"clue","img":"icons/sundries/books/book-worn-brown.webp","system":{"description":"A large black leather book meticulously maintained by William the Man of Law, Bardolf Greed's trusted lawyer. William records everything during Bardolf's meetings and interviews. This book contains detailed accounts of all of Bardolf's business dealings, both legal and illicit, including the management of both the Factories and mine. The book could contain evidence of Greed's shady business practices, worker exploitation, starvation wages, and the circumstances surrounding the mine collapse.","location":"William the Man of Law carries it at all times","importance":"important","found":false,"scenario":"the-city-of-pigs"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"a8019db557ca286e","name":"Grotesque Pig Masks","type":"object","img":"icons/equipment/head/mask-carved-pig.webp","system":{"description":"Macabre pig masks worn by the revolutionary gang called the Pig Heads, led by the three Browne brothers. These grotesque masks hide the identities of the gang members as they terrorize Whitehaven, kidnapping and injuring Bardolf Greed's factory workers. The masks are a symbol of their transformation and rebellion, representing both their literal mutations from consuming The God's flesh and their symbolic rejection of being treated like animals by Greed's exploitative industries. When gang members activate their powers, their heads physically become pig-like, making the masks unnecessary.","quantity":1,"weight":1,"value":20,"equipped":false,"properties":["Disguise","Gang symbol","Intimidating","Hides identity"]},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"d24b4d211a21dbdf","name":"Flesh of The God Under the Mine","type":"object","img":"icons/consumables/meat/organ-heart-red.webp","system":{"description":"Pieces of divine flesh torn from the enormous pig-like head of The God Under the Mine embedded in the rock below Whitehaven. This regenerating meat confers incredible powers to those who consume it: superhuman strength, enhanced endurance, rapid healing, and the ability to transform into monstrous pig-headed beings. Arthur Browne discovered this flesh while trapped underground and has been feeding it to miners through Frank's slaughterhouse, creating an army of Pig Heads. The flesh can spawn grotesque tentacled abominations and grants temporary power boosts, but prolonged consumption leads to loss of control and mutation.","quantity":1,"weight":1,"value":2000,"equipped":false,"properties":["Magical","Divine","Regenerating","Grants mutations","Corrupting influence","Heals wounds"]},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"ef22aff728cd0858","name":"Frank's Mechanical Pincer Arm","type":"object","img":"icons/equipment/hand/gauntlet-metal-reinforced-steel.webp","system":{"description":"A home-made mechanical arm with a powerful pincer claw, created by Frank Browne to replace the arm and leg he lost during the catastrophic mine collapse. This ingenious device has multiple functions: the pincer can crush with enough force to inflict severe wounds, and it features a built-in pulley system that can launch from the arm to raise or lower Frank about thirty feet, carrying up to two additional people. The mechanical arm is a testament to Frank's determination and his role as the strongarm of the Pig Heads gang.","quantity":1,"weight":8,"value":600,"equipped":true,"properties":["Mechanical","Prosthetic","Crushing grip","Grappling hook","Custom-built","Multi-functional"]},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
